cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper discusses privacy-preserving analytics, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of Federated Learning for private analytics suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The decentralized nature of the framework suggests that it may also fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the evaluation of the framework using varying model sizes and use cases suggests that it may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
